gate: LOCKED
v:4 role:dev x:nextjs-tailwind
task: S03 T7 — #1291 Variant selector polish: brand fallback + smoke checklist + banner test
requires: [NEXTJS_VERCEL_FRONTEND]
sprint: S03
repos: [crop-front]
branch: issue-1291

context: |
  3 polish sub-tasks from #158 deferred at MVP ship. All verified accurate against dev (2026-06-01).
  Domain primer:
  - Variant = a distinct configuration of the same model family (e.g. NH T6.155 has 11 variants)
  - humaniseBrand() in lib/brand-display-names.ts maps short-code prefixes (Nhl, Cih) to human names
  - extractBrand() in variants-brand-filter.tsx does NOT currently use humaniseBrand()
  - Test data: 1-variant = ford-7710; multi-variant = new-holland-t6155-autocommand-stage-v (11 variants)
  - Unit test pattern: app/equipment/[slug]/_components/__tests__/equipment-variants-banner.test.tsx
  All 3 sub-tasks ship in one PR from branch issue-1291.

steps:
  1. Branch: git checkout -b issue-1291 dev

  SUB-TASK 1 — Brand-name fallback (small):
    a. app/equipment/[slug]/variants/_components/variants-brand-filter.tsx:88-94:
       Wrap extractBrand() return values in humaniseBrand() from @/lib/brand-display-names.
       Pattern: humaniseBrand(extractBrand(displayName, modelNumber))
    b. app/equipment/[slug]/variants/__tests__/variants-brand-filter.test.tsx:
       Add test cases:
         - extractBrand('Nhl 1100', '1100') → 'New Holland' (after humaniseBrand wrapping)
         - extractBrand('Cih 7250', '7250') → 'Case IH'
    c. Verify: bun test variants-brand-filter

  SUB-TASK 2 — Manual smoke checklist (small):
    a. Create docs/smoke/variant-selector.md with 3 walkthroughs:
       - 1-variant model (ford-7710):
           detail page shows NO "Compare N other variants" banner
           /equipment/ford-7710/variants URL 308-redirects to the single variant
       - Multi-variant model (new-holland-t6155-autocommand-stage-v):
           banner renders with correct count
           /variants page lists all variants
       - 0-variant model: if none exists in live data, document that and note it's
         covered via integration test mock (sub-task 3) instead
    b. Walk the checklist on the PR's Vercel preview → check the boxes in the committed file.
       (The committed file with checked boxes IS the verification artifact for this sub-task.)

  SUB-TASK 3 — Banner-slot integration test (small):
    a. Create app/equipment/[slug]/_components/__tests__/equipment-detail.test.tsx
    b. Tests:
         - EquipmentDetail with variantsBanner={<div data-testid="banner"/>} → banner present in DOM
         - EquipmentDetail with variantsBanner={null} → absent
       Copy async server-rendered pattern from equipment-variants-banner.test.tsx.
    c. Verify: bun test equipment-detail
    d. Note: e2e already covers banner visibility on live data (equipment-variants.spec.ts:99-123);
       this integration test covers layout composition in isolation — both are wanted.

  3. Commit(s): polish(variants): apply humaniseBrand to extractBrand filter (#1291)
                polish(variants): add manual smoke checklist for variant selector (#1291)
                polish(variants): add banner-slot integration test for EquipmentDetail (#1291)
     (One PR is fine; 3 commits or squash — your call.)
  4. Open draft PR into dev, reference #1291.
     Before marking ready: walk the smoke checklist on the Vercel preview and check the boxes.

cmd:
  - bun run lint:fix
  - bun run type-check
  - bunx vitest run app/equipment/\[slug\]/variants/__tests__/variants-brand-filter.test.tsx
  - bunx vitest run app/equipment/\[slug\]/_components/__tests__/equipment-detail.test.tsx
  - bun run check:all

out:
  - app/equipment/[slug]/variants/_components/variants-brand-filter.tsx (humaniseBrand applied)
  - app/equipment/[slug]/variants/__tests__/variants-brand-filter.test.tsx (new cases added)
  - docs/smoke/variant-selector.md (checklist created + walked)
  - app/equipment/[slug]/_components/__tests__/equipment-detail.test.tsx (new test file)

done:
  - humaniseBrand wraps extractBrand output — Nhl → New Holland, Cih → Case IH
  - vitest passes for variants-brand-filter + equipment-detail tests
  - Smoke checklist committed with all boxes checked (walked on Vercel preview)
  - bun run check:all clean
  - PR draft open against dev; closure authority: Vova confirms smoke checklist fidelity
